result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Vincent James Skinaway

records.addlTxt: 8:33 AM Defendant Vincent James Skinaway appeared by video, in custody from Sawyer County Jail.  Attorney Stephanie E Thomas-Schmidt in court for Vincent James Skinaway.  Attorney Jennifer Gross in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case and recites appearances.   Attny Thomas-Schmidt indicates DEF to waive extradition.  Court reviews the extradition complaint.   DEF agrees he is the person Anoka MN is looking for.   Court advised him as to his right to waive or contest extradition.  Court goes through Waiver of Extradition with DEF.    DEF waives extradition.  Court finds DEF has freely waived his right of extradition - DEF signs document through video conference and DEF remain in custody to await transport to MN.
